# OpenCode Plugins Skill

Create OpenCode plugins that hook into 25+ events across the AI assistant lifecycle.

## Plugin Structure

```
# Global plugins (all projects)
~/.config/opencode/plugin/my-plugin.js

# Project plugins (current project only)
project/.opencode/plugin/my-plugin.js
```

## Basic Template

```javascript
export const MyPlugin = async (context) => {
  // context: { project, client, $, directory, worktree }
  
  return {
    event: async ({ event }) => {
      switch (event.type) {
        case "file.edited":
          // Handle file edits
          break;
        case "tool.execute.before":
          // Pre-process tool execution
          break;
        case "tool.execute.after":
          // Post-process tool execution
          break;
      }
    },
  };
};
```

## Key Events

### File Events
| Event | Data |
|-------|------|
| `file.edited` | `{ path, content, timestamp }` |
| `file.watcher.updated` | `{ path, type }` |

### Tool Events
| Event | Data |
|-------|------|
| `tool.execute.before` | `{ tool, args, user }` |
| `tool.execute.after` | `{ tool, duration, success, output }` |

### Permission Events
| Event | Data |
|-------|------|
| `permission.replied` | `{ action, target, decision }` |

### Session Events
| Event | Data |
|-------|------|
| `session.created` | `{ sessionId }` |
| `session.idle` | `{ sessionId, duration }` |

## Common Patterns

### Environment File Protection
```javascript
export const EnvProtectionPlugin = async ({ project }) => {
  const sensitivePatterns = [/\.env$/, /credentials\.json$/];
  
  return {
    event: async ({ event }) => {
      if (event.type === "file.edited") {
        if (sensitivePatterns.some(p => p.test(event.data.path))) {
          console.warn(`Warning: Sensitive file edited: ${event.data.path}`);
        }
      }
    },
  };
};
```

### Auto-Format on Save
```javascript
export const AutoFormatPlugin = async ({ $ }) => {
  return {
    event: async ({ event }) => {
      if (event.type === "file.edited" && /\.(js|ts|tsx)$/.test(event.data.path)) {
        await $`prettier --write ${event.data.path}`;
      }
    },
  };
};
```

## Best Practices

- Use `async` handlers (don't block)
- Wrap in try/catch (don't crash)
- Defer heavy work to background
- Don't log sensitive data
- One plugin per concern
